    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113488-general/topic/Lean.20vs.20Litex.3A.20Formalize.20irrationality.20of.20.E2.88.9A2.20and.20.20.E2.84.9D.20.E2.88.88.20Group/near/527708790\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In your second example, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Float.add_assoc#doc\">docs#Float.add_assoc</a> not only doesn't exist, but is false</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thank you for your comment, Eric. I removed the float example. The reason why I want to prove that both ℝ and ℤ are groups is that function type narrowing is automatic in Litex, which is very convenient and uncommon in most formal languages.</p>",
        "id": 527716304,
