    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"511228\">Huỳnh Trần Khanh</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113488-general/topic/Lean.20vs.20Litex.3A.20Formalize.20irrationality.20of.20.E2.88.9A2.20and.20.20.E2.84.9D.20.E2.88.88.20Group/near/527919462\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Color me skeptical</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Litex have other keywords <code>exist</code>, <code>have</code>, <code>exist_prop</code>.  <code>exist</code> <code>exist_prop</code> ensures existence. <code>have</code> ensures the new object is introduced with its existence ensured. In this case, for clarity of explanation, I just use the \"unsafe\" keyword fn as example. I am working on Litex reference manual, the detailed explanations will be on that.  Thank you Khanh.</p>",
        "id": 527988272,
        "sender_full_name": "Jackie Shen",
        "timestamp": 1752111136
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"511228\">Huỳnh Trần Khanh</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113488-general/topic/Lean.20vs.20Litex.3A.20Formalize.20irrationality.20of.20.E2.88.9A2.20and.20.20.E2.84.9D.20.E2.88.88.20Group/near/527919615\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If fn axiomatically defines a function then what is the syntax for defining a function that doesn't contradict the existing foundation</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>LItex uses naive set theory (see first 4 chapters of Terry Tao's Analysis One) as foundation. The axioms ensures existance of functions, sets when they are defined properly.</p>",
        "id": 527988417,
        "sender_full_name": "Jackie Shen",
        "timestamp": 1752111266
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's a proof that the real number 114 is equal to the real number 514 in Litex:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">forall</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">claim</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">forall</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">prove</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">claim</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mi\">114</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">514</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">prove</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">514</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/H-57qBO09IKwKwU1LXu3nqc7/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/H-57qBO09IKwKwU1LXu3nqc7/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"479x627\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/H-57qBO09IKwKwU1LXu3nqc7/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
